The paper discusses the development of a dataset for document layout analysis using deep neural networks, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV). The dataset is created by matching XML representations and content of over 1 million PDF articles, which involves information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The use of deep neural networks for analyzing document layout also falls under deep learning (cs.DL) and machine learning (cs.LG).
